ng rates hourly based on the difference between perpetual and oracle prices, with payments occurring every hour rather than the standard 8-hour cycle. The platform's GLP and GM liquidity pools act as counterparties to traders, creating a different dynamic where funding rates reflect imbalances between long and short positions. Oracle dependency means funding rates can deviate from spot market premiums, especially during high volatility periods when oracle updates lag price movements."}]]}],"$L3",["$L4","$L5","$L6"],"$L7"]}],"$L8"]}]]}],["$L9","$La"],"$Lb"]}],"loading":null,"isPartial":false}
3:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","JTO","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"JTO's moderate volatility and growing DeFi adoption make it suitable for funding rate strategies on GMX's unique infrastructure. The pair's relatively small trading volume on GMX means funding rates can become more extreme during directional moves, creating arbitrage windows against centralized exchanges with different funding mechanisms."}]]}]
4:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"JTO/USDT funding rates on GMX typically range from -0.5% to +1.2% annually, with higher volatility during Solana ecosystem events or broader DeFi market movements. The hourly settlement cycle creates more frequent but smaller funding payments compared to 8-hour cycles on CEXs. During strong uptrends, funding rates often spike above 0.8% annually as retail traders favor long positions, while bear markets see rates turn negative as institutional players hedge exposure."}]]}]
5:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The most profitable JTO funding arbitrage occurs during divergence between GMX and major CEX rates, particularly when oracle lag creates temporary mispricings. Cross-DEX arbitrage with other Arbitrum-based perpetual platforms like Gains Network can be effective due to shared infrastructure but different pricing mechanisms. Position sizes should remain moderate given GMX's price impact on larger trades and the need to maintain delta neutrality across platforms."}]]}]
6:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Oracle dependency poses the primary risk, as Chainlink price feeds can lag during extreme volatility, creating funding rate distortions. GMX's 0.05%-0.07% trading fees are higher than most CEXs, requiring careful calculation of break-even funding rate differentials. The platform's battle-tested track record since 2021 provides confidence, but smart contract risk remains inherent to DeFi protocols, especially when maintaining positions across multiple platforms for arbitrage."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lc",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are JTO funding rates calculated on GMX?","answer":"GMX calculates and settles funding rates every hour for JTO/USDT perpetuals, unlike the 8-hour cycles common on centralized exchanges. This creates 24 funding events per day and requires more frequent monitoring for arbitrage strategies."},{"question":"What causes JTO funding rate spikes on GMX?","answer":"Funding rate spikes typically occur when there's a significant imbalance between long and short positions, often triggered by Solana ecosystem news or when oracle prices lag behind rapid market movements. The platform's smaller liquidity compared to major CEXs can amplify these effects."},{"question":"Can I arbitrage JTO funding rates between GMX and Binance?","answer":"Yes, but you must account for GMX's hourly vs Binance's 8-hour funding cycles, different calculation methods, and the higher trading fees on GMX. Success requires precise timing and sufficient position sizes to overcome fee differences while maintaining delta neutrality."},{"question":"What's the maximum position size for JTO on GMX?","answer":"Position limits depend on the available liquidity in GM pools for JTO, which varies based on pool composition and utilization. Large positions may experience significant price impact due to GMX's AMM-style pricing model, making funding arbitrage less profitable at scale."}]}]
